00:06:22.600 --> 00:06:26.240
I said, where is
the vega report?

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:27.680
So, let me show you.

00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:33.050
So that's the story.

00:06:36.102 --> 00:06:39.060
So I'm obviously not going
to tell you the story of Pi

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:40.130
or "Life of Pi."

00:06:40.130 --> 00:06:42.830
That's not a financial story.

00:06:42.830 --> 00:06:45.460
The rest of the story,
alpha, beta, delta, gamma,

00:06:45.460 --> 00:06:49.450
theta, which you will learn
from Peter and Choongbum

00:06:49.450 --> 00:06:50.980
and Vasily's classes.

00:06:50.980 --> 00:06:53.079
So I'm going to talk about vega.

00:06:53.079 --> 00:06:54.870
So by the way, before
I tell you the story,

00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:57.794
what's unique about
vega on this list?

00:06:57.794 --> 00:06:59.210
AUDIENCE: It's not
a Greek letter.

00:06:59.210 --> 00:07:00.626
JAKE XIA: It's not
a Greek letter.

00:07:00.626 --> 00:07:02.070
That's right.

00:07:02.070 --> 00:07:04.390
So I turned around and
asked my desk quant, I said,

00:07:04.390 --> 00:07:05.860
where's the vega report?

00:07:05.860 --> 00:07:09.862
But how many of you actually
know what a vega is?

00:07:09.862 --> 00:07:10.820
OK, lot of people know.

00:07:10.820 --> 00:07:13.720
So anyway, I'm not
going to-- just

00:07:13.720 --> 00:07:16.490
for the people who haven't
heard about it before, it's

00:07:16.490 --> 00:07:20.230
a measurement about
a book or portfolio

00:07:20.230 --> 00:07:22.930
or position's sensitivity
to volatility.

00:07:22.930 --> 00:07:24.400
So, what is volatility?

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:29.480
Which again, you will learn
more in rigorous terms

00:07:29.480 --> 00:07:31.440
how it's defined in mathematics.

00:07:31.440 --> 00:07:36.040
